track_notes: Nice walk, not difficult, 14km long. You can reach the point just in the middle of the two summits, by bicycle riding on the large forest road. To reach my starting point, you need a 4x4 wheel car (or hight wheel car). You must follow the yellow mark. Nice view all around.

This track was in winter but it was no snow or ice. There is a small car park. As you start to walk, the sloope is very hard. There is enought room on the two summits for antenna and the view is wonderfull.
